"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.5.3.11\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.5.3.11</span> Embroidered cloth, needlework</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">מַעֲשֶׂה, רקם</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(ma‘aseh roqem)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:36\">EXO 26:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod27:16\">EXO 27:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:39\">EXO 28:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod36:37\">EXO 36:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod38:18\">EXO 38:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:29\">EXO 39:29</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">רִקְמָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(riqmah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:30\">JDG 5:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:30\">JDG 5:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:15\">PSA 45:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:10\">EZK 16:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:13\">EZK 16:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:18\">EZK 16:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:16\">EZK 26:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:7\">EZK 27:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:16\">EZK 27:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:24\">EZK 27:24</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">ποικιλτής</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(poikiltēs)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir45:10\">SIR 45:10</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0349_embroidered_cloth.jpg\" alt=\"Linen cloth embroidered with wool\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">Linen cloth embroidered with wool (© EgyArt, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>Embroidered cloth was cloth into which decorative patterns or figures were sewn by hand. Because of the extra work that went into it, embroidered cloth was expensive.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>Where there is no word for “embroidery,” it is possible to use a descriptive expression; for example, in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:36\">EXO 26:36</a><abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr> has “Someone who can sew well is to sew designs on it,” and in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:7\">EZK 27:7</a> it says “linen with designs sewed on it.” Where even this is difficult to express in the receptor language, translators may say simply “fancy linen” or “decorated cloth.”</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
